[ 摘要 ] 


本研究目的在於檢驗視覺傳達設計課程應用於提升高職烘焙科學生創造性思考的可行性。以視覺傳達設計理論為基礎，設計24堂教學，以臺南市私立天主教慈幼工商烘焙食品科學生為實驗對象。創造力發展與認知形式的發展在個體發生層次上具有普遍性，因此研究者以高二50位學生為實驗組，高三50位學生為對照組，正式樣本共100位。本研究的創造力量測，採用林幸台、王木榮（1994）修訂的「威廉斯創造力測驗」的「創造性思考活動測驗」。為比較實驗組與對照組創造力得分的差距是否有差異，採用共變數分析，並以前測分數做為控制變項，實驗組部分以態度作為調節變項；研究結果，實驗組創造力的表現顯著高於對照組，且在開放性及標題命名創造力發展上尤為顯著；對於烘焙實習作品的做工、創意性、設計感（商品化）、細緻度、主題性等「後測表現」顯著優於「前測表現」。透過此準實驗設計的結果，可推論在高職的烘焙課程融入「視覺傳達設計課程」時，學生會有較佳的創造能力展現。 

[ 英文摘要 ] 


The purpose of this study was to examine the feasibility of applying visual communication design programs to enhance students’ creative thinking ability toward Baking department at the Vocational high school. This study employed visual communication design theory and designed 24 teaching lessons upon private Catholic Salesian Tainan Science Industrial and Commercial High School students.Creativity and cognitive development of individual forms of development was popular on teaching methods. Therefore, this research conducted high school eleven graders as the experimental group and twelve graders as the control group, total effective 100 respondents were acquired. Creativity measurement mechanism adapted Hsin-Tai Lin and Wang Mu-rong (1994) revised from "Williams creativity test" and "divergent thinking tests."This study used ANOVA and the previous test scores as control variables to compare the experimental group and control group to see whether any significant difference between creativity scores. The results of the experimental group significantly higher than creative performance. Through the quasi-experimental design results on vocational baking courses could predict that" visual communication design program", students generated better creative performance.


